Objective: 
To understand and implement JavaScript functions and array operations, including function declarations, function expressions, and various array methods.
Problem Statement: 
Write an HTML and JavaScript program that demonstrates the use of JavaScript functions and arrays. The program should include:
•	A function declaration to greet a person by name.
•	A function expression to calculate the square of a number.
•	Array operations, including accessing elements, iterating over an array, and using array methods 


Procedure:
1.	Open your text editor or IDE.
2.	Create a new HTML file and add the following code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>JavaScript Functions and Arrays</title>
</head>
<body>
    <script>
        // Function declaration
        function greet(name) {
            return "Hello, " + name + "!";
        }

        // Function expression
        const square = function(number) {
            return number * number;
        };

        // Testing functions
        console.log(greet("Alice"));
        console.log("Square of 4:", square(4));

        // Array operations
        let fruits = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry"];

        // Accessing elements
        console.log("First fruit:", fruits[0]);
        console.log("Second fruit:", fruits[1]);

        // Iterating over an array
        console.log("Fruits list:");
        for (let i = 0; i < fruits.length; i++) {
            console.log(fruits[i]);
        }

        // Array methods
        fruits.push("Kiwi", "Lemon");
        console.log("Fruits after push:", fruits);

        let fruitIndex = fruits.indexOf("Banana");
        console.log("Index of Banana:", fruitIndex);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
3.	Save the file with a .html extension
4.	Open the saved HTML file in your web browser to view the output. To see the console output, open the browser's developer tools (by pressing F12 or right-clicking on the page and selecting "Inspect" or "Inspect Element"), and navigate to the "Console" tab.
